her than mitigating violence. Chaturvedi traces these dynamics from the late colonial period to the early 2000s, illuminating the broader relationships between democratic life, divisiveness, and majoritarianism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 0aDemocracyzIndia, South. 0aPolitical partieszIndiazKerala. 0aPolitical violencezIndiazCannanore (District). 0aRight and left (Political science)zIndiazKerala. 7aHISTORY / Asia / South / India.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311099775040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478024606?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478024606423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478024606/original  a978-3-11-099775-0  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles